nd and they do need to be answered in a particular way.  So, please do not hesitate to ask me.\\r\\n \\r\\nAs your support tutor, I would like to get to know a little about you first, so that I can get a feel of how to best support you through your studies.\\r\\n\\r\\nPlease could you provide me with the following details:\\r\\n\\u2022\\tYour experience \\/ background so far in the child care or education sector\\r\\n\\u2022\\tWhere you are gaining your practical experience for your course\\r\\n\\u2022\\tThe hours\\/sessions that you either work or volunteer for your practical experience\\r\\n\\u2022\\tWhat type of child care or education that involves, ie child minding, cr\\u00e8che, play group, day care, schools etc.\\r\\n\\u2022\\tPlease also let me know what Unit you are currently working on\\r\\n \\r\\nI look forward to hearing from you soon, and starting the process of supporting you through your studies.\\r\\n\\r\\n\"}', 1513788320, 1, 0, 0),
(51, 28, 76, '{\"Message\":\"Hello Nahida\\r\\n\\r\\nMy name is Linda Broome-Smith, and I have been allocated as your tutor.  Please allow me to introduce myself to you.\\r\\n\\r\\nI have worked in the childcare sector for many years.  I have managed my own preschool, worked as a childminder and also worked in full day care nurseries, and schools throughout my career.\\r\\n\\r\\nAs a tutor and an assessor, I have taught a range of different levels and types of child care and supporting teaching and learning in schools courses, both in the classroom and on line.  I have also taught a range of management and leadership courses, in order to help others to possess the relevant skills to both effectively manage people and business matters. \\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nI have always enjoyed working alongside my students, supporting them to achieve their qualifications, to enjoy their learning experience and fulfil their wish to become more informed professional childcare practitioners.\\r\\n\\r\\nIt is now my privilege to have been allocated to you, as your tutor support, whilst studying for your:\\r\\n\\r\\nLevel 4 \\u2013 Certificate for Higher Level Teaching Assistants\\r\\n\\r\\nDistance learning has a lot of benefits.  It allows you to read and research at a pace which suits you, and allows you to keep your working hours and to complete your evidence at a pace that suits you.  However, the pace must always be moving steadily ahead, in order for you to complete all the work needed before the end of your course.  \\r\\n \\r\\nPlease do not forget that I am here to help you to succeed in your studies.  Therefore please never slow down or be stuck with your studies, due to not understanding what the evidence criteria is asking of you, or how to find information that may help you achieve the criteria.    \\r\\n \\r\\nThis is exactly the time when you should contact me, in order to ask for any advice or support you may need.  Some of the criteria (questions) are tricky to understand and they do need to be answered in a particular way.  So, please do not hesitate to ask me.\\r\\n \\r\\nAs your support tutor, I would like to get to know a little about you first, so that I can get a feel of how to best support you through your studies.\\r\\n\\r\\nPlease could you provide me with the following details:\\r\\n\\u2022\\tYour experience \\/ background so far in the child care or education sector\\r\\n\\u2022\\tWhere you are gaining your practical experience for your course\\r\\n\\u2022\\tThe hours\\/sessions that you either work or volunteer for your practical experience\\r\\n\\u2022\\tWhat type of child care or education that involves, ie child minding, cr\\u00e8che, play group, day care, schools etc.\\r\\n\\u2022\\tPlease also let me know what Unit you are currently working on\\r\\n \\r\\nI look forward to hearing from you soon, and starting the process of supporting you through your studies.\\r\\n\\r\\n\"}', 1513788349, 0, 0, 0),
(52, 45, 28, '{\"Message\":\"<p>I do apologise for not returning your e-mail. Nice to read your messages actually. I have been working hard this month, so i just got this chance to reply back now. Once this month is over i will have time to study this course. So please be patient with me. Thank you<\\/p>\"}', 1513796193, 1, 0, 0),
(53, 82, 28, '{\"Message\":\"<p>Hello Linda, i have various previous experience inside a classroom and also in a nursery which i did threw getting ready for work programs. i have also had experience with adults with learning difficulties and other disabilities while i was volunteering at a social night for them which i did for about 3 years. i have previously been to college as well where i studied NC child health and social care which looked at the aspects of child development and behavior along with psychology, sociology and first aid. i am aiming to be a primary school teacher one day and thought this was my best opportunity to get my foot threw the door as they say. I\'m currently not doing anything child care or educational related I\'m currently working as a bartender which takes up the majority of my time at the moment so i am no longer volunteering either. I haven\'t started the course work as of yet i just looked through it today i will be making a start on it tomorrow and will just be starting with the first aspect on my list which i believe is the section on ADHD. thanks for your message and i will be in touch if i need your assistance. thank you.<\\/p><p>from Shannon.<\\/p>\"}', 1513802355, 1, 0, 0),
(54, 28, 45, '{\"Message\":\"<p>Hello there<\\/p><p>Lovely to hear from you.&nbsp; <\\/p><p>I was only getting concerned that the messages were not getting through to you.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\\/p><p>I am sure you are very busy, especially this time of year.<\\/p><p>I am just pleased that the communication is working between us properly.<\\/p><p>I have your name as King Wah Peter Yip<\\/p><p>I just wanted to know how you would like to be addressed in emails please.<\\/p><p>Regards<\\/p><p>Linda<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p>\"}', 1513858508, 1, 0, 0),
(55, 28, 82, '{\"Message\":\"<p>Hello Shannon<\\/p><p>Lovely to hear from you,and thank you for your quick reply.<\\/p><p>You have some past experience, which I am sure will help you with your studies.&nbsp; As this is a knowledge and understanding based course though, there is much to read and research which will no doubt be interesting for you to do.<\\/p><p>If in the future you would like to pursue a career as a Teaching Assistant, the four modules you are taking are also able to be used in the NCC\'s Level 3 qualifications&nbsp;<\\/p><p>I am about to send some advice sheets to you, and I hope they will be useful for your studies.<\\/p><p>In the meantime, if there is anything that you would like advice on, please do not hesitate to ask me<\\/p><p>Regards<\\/p><p>Linda&nbsp;<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p>\"}', 1513858898, 1, 0, 0);
