(63, 28, 45, '{\"Message\":\"<p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" align=\\\"center\\\" style=\\\"text-align:center\\\"><b><u><span style=\\\"font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;color:red\\\">Advice for\\r\\nanswering your course questions effectively<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/u><\\/b><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" align=\\\"center\\\" style=\\\"text-align:center\\\"><b><u><span style=\\\"font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;color:red\\\"><o:p><span style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none;\\\">&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/u><\\/b><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\">In your studies, you will be challenged to show your\\r\\nknowledge and understanding of particular topics in the form of questions to\\r\\nanswer.&nbsp; <\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\">Whilst answering the criteria, you will need to provide evidence\\r\\nof your knowledge and understanding of the topic set.<\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\">In order to challenge you in this way, the criteria are\\r\\nworded in particular ways, and it is extremely important that you present your\\r\\nevidence in the particular way it has been set.&nbsp;\\r\\nIf you do not, you might find that your work is referred back to you due\\r\\nto the answer not being fully met in the way it was asked to be presented.<\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\">Please have a look at the tips provided below, and also look\\r\\nthrough the <b><span style=\\\"color:#7030A0\\\">\\u2018Glossary\\r\\nof Terms\\u2019<\\/span><\\/b> that I have also sent, in order to help you to understand\\r\\nthe ways in which the questions should be answered.<\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\">If you need any further help, please do not hesitate to ask\\r\\nme.<\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\"><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype\\r\\n id=\\\"_x0000_t75\\\" coordsize=\\\"21600,21600\\\" o:spt=\\\"75\\\" o:preferrelative=\\\"t\\\"\\r\\n path=\\\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\\\" filled=\\\"f\\\" stroked=\\\"f\\\">\\r\\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\\\"miter\\\"\\/>\\r\\n <v:formulas>\\r\\n  <v:f eqn=\\\"