(70, 28, 82, '{\"Message\":\"<p><span style=\\\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\\\">Hello\\r\\nShannon<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-top: 1rem; margin-right: 1rem; margin-left: 1rem;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\\\">I hope that you had a wonderful\\r\\nChristmas and New Year<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-top: 1rem; margin-right: 1rem; margin-left: 1rem;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\\\">The Unit 1 is all about\\r\\nchildren\'s development and your knowledge of the ages and stages of\\r\\ndevelopment.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-top: 1rem; margin-right: 1rem; margin-left: 1rem;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\\\">If you have particular questions,\\r\\nthat you are concerned about, can you please let me know the actual criteria\\r\\nnumbers, so that I can be sure what you are asking advice on?<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-top: 1rem; margin-right: 1rem; margin-left: 1rem;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\\\">You have said the last 5\\r\\nquestions, so I will try to explain these for you<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-top: 1rem; margin-right: 1rem; margin-left: 1rem;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\\\">1.4.1 \\u2013&nbsp;this is asking you\\r\\nto consider the importance of early detection of speech, language and\\r\\ncommunication problems.&nbsp; If children have\\r\\nproblems in this area of development and are not quickly referred for help, how\\r\\nwill this affect the rest of their development areas?&nbsp; If you type the actual question into a search\\r\\nengine of your choice, you will find lots of information on the internet you\\r\\nhelp you with this.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\\\">1.4.2\\r\\n\\u2013 this question is asking you to explain, by using am example, of how\\r\\nmulti-agencies can work together in order to help communication, language and speck\\r\\nproblems.&nbsp; Think about how you might have\\r\\nnoticed, spoken to the parents, involved the SENCO and then speech therapists etc.&nbsp; How all of these people can work together to\\r\\nhelp the child to develop these skills..&nbsp;\\r\\nIf you type the actual question into a search engine of your choice, you\\r\\nwill find lots of information on the internet you help you with this.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\\\">1.4.3\\r\\n\\u2013 this question is asking you to show your knowledge of how different types of\\r\\nplay and activities can help a child to develop their speech, language and\\r\\ncommunication<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\\\">Make\\r\\nsure that you think of all three areas her and the types of play activities\\r\\nwhich may help. If you type the actual question into a search engine of your\\r\\nchoice, you will find lots of information on the internet you help you with\\r\\nthis.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\\\">1.5.1\\r\\n\\u2013 this question is asking you to look at a variety of transitions that affect\\r\\nchildren\\u2019s or young people\\u2019s development.&nbsp;\\r\\nYou need to look at the UNIT 1 again for this information or If you type\\r\\nthe actual question into a search engine of your choice, you will find lots of\\r\\ninformation on the internet you help you with this.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\\\">You\\r\\nneed to list the types of transitions and then briefly explain individually how\\r\\neach of these might affect the child \\/ young person<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\\\">1.5.2\\r\\n\\u2013 this question is asking you to evaluate how people who are helping the child\\r\\ncan have a positive affect when they are going through these periods of\\r\\ntransition.&nbsp; This goes hand in hand with\\r\\nthe work that you would have produced in 1.5.1&nbsp;\\r\\n<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\\\"><o:p>&nbsp;<\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\\\">I\\r\\nhope this helps.&nbsp; I do not want you to feel\\r\\nthat this course is too much for you.&nbsp;\\r\\nThere are Level 3 books that you can either buy or borrow from the\\r\\nlibrary about Supporting Teaching and Learning in Schools which might also give\\r\\nyou some extra information. If not as I say, If you type the actual question\\r\\ninto a search engine of your choice, you will find lots of information on the\\r\\ninternet you help you with this.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\\\">Please\\r\\nask again if you need any further help<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\\\">Regards<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\\\">Linda\\r\\n<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\\\"><o:p>&nbsp;<\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\\\"><o:p>&nbsp;<\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\\\"><o:p>&nbsp;<\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\\\"><o:p>&nbsp;<\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\\\"><o:p>&nbsp;<\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\