(161, 24, 118, '{\"Message\":\"<p>Hi Chelsea,<\\/p><p>There is no word count so you can write as much as you like. However, try to keep to the point and be specific with your responses.&nbsp;<\\/p><p>The response boxes do not indicate how much you need to write as some responses could be a few lines and others a page.&nbsp;<\\/p><p>I would suggest you look at how the questions are worded eg if you are asked to discuss or evaluate then these responses may be a little longer than being asked to explain.&nbsp;<\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size: 1rem;\\\">I hope this makes sense. If you are still unsure, let me know.<\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size: 1rem;\\\">Best wishes<\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size: 1rem;\\\">Allison&nbsp;&nbsp;<\\/span><br><\\/p>\"}', 1516304718, 1, 0, 0),
(162, 135, 28, '{\"Message\":\"<p>Hello Linda.&nbsp; Thank you for taking the time out to message me. I am really looking forward to starting this course, but also a bit apprehensive, as I am now 34 years old, so a bit rusty when it comes to learning new things! This course however, is something I\'ve been interested in for a while. As far as my experience is concerned, I have a 6 year old daughter in Year 1. I have absolutely no experience in the classroom, but I do however help out on school trips. If I feel like volunteering in a classroom will benefit me in regards to my course, that shouldn\'t be a problem as I live in very close range to 6 primary schools. I will be starting with Unit 1, and won\'t hesitate to message you with any help I may need.<\\/p><p>Thanks again - Gemma<\\/p>\"}', 1516354936, 1, 0, 0),
(163, 28, 135, '{\"Message\":\"<p>Hello Gemma<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Thank you for responding to my welcome email so quickly<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Although you have no experience as yet, this course will help you with the fundamentals of work as a Teaching Assistant.&nbsp; Although a placement is not required for this course, volunteering would allow you to understand the Teaching Assistant role better.&nbsp; Lots of students do, just to get a feel for things.&nbsp; But it is up to you.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>The Level 3 \\u2013 Supporting Teaching and Learning in Schools AWARD, is a great start to your journey as a qualified Teaching Assistant.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>The course will encourage you to read and research for the information needed in order to answer the questions, and allow your study skills to develop.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Later, if you decide to further your training to a full&nbsp; Level 2 or Level 3 Supporting Teaching and Learning in Schools Qualification, these units will be of great use t you.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>I look forward to working alongside you in your studies Gemma<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>If you have any questions, please feel free to ask me<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>I will now be sending you some further emails with Advice Sheets for you to look at.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>I hope you will find them useful for your studies.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Bye for now<\\/p><div><br><\\/div>\"}', 1516361631, 1, 0, 0),
