(261, 28, 189, '{\"Message\":\"Hello Abbie\\r\\n\\r\\nMy name is Linda Broome-Smith, and I have been allocated as your tutor.  Please allow me to introduce myself to you.\\r\\n\\r\\nI have worked in the childcare sector for many years.  I have managed my own preschool, worked as a childminder and also worked in full day care nurseries, and schools throughout my career.\\r\\n\\r\\nAs a tutor and an assessor, I have taught a range of different levels and types of child care and supporting teaching and learning in schools courses, both in the classroom and on line.  I have also taught a range of management and leadership courses, in order to help others to possess the relevant skills to both effectively manage people and business matters. \\r\\n\\r\\nI have always enjoyed working alongside my students, supporting them to achieve their qualifications, to enjoy their learning experience and fulfil their wish to become more informed professional childcare practitioners.\\r\\n\\r\\nIt is now my privilege to have been allocated to you, as your tutor support, whilst studying for your:\\r\\n\\r\\nLevel 3 \\u2013 Supporting Teaching and Learning in Schools \\u2013 Award\\r\\nDistance learning has a lot of benefits.  It allows you to read and research at a pace which suits you, and allows you to keep your working hours and to complete your evidence at a pace that suits you.  However, the pace must always be moving steadily ahead, in order for you to complete all the work needed before the end of your course.  \\r\\n \\r\\nPlease do not forget that I am here to help you to succeed in your studies.  Therefore please never slow down or be stuck with your studies, due to not understanding what the evidence criteria is asking of you, or how to find information that may help you achieve the criteria.    \\r\\n \\r\\nThis is exactly the time when you should contact me, in order to ask for any advice or support you may need.  Some of the criteria (questions) are tricky to understand and they do need to be answered in a particular way.  So, please do not hesitate to ask me.\\r\\n \\r\\nAs your support tutor, I would like to get to know a little about you first, so that I can get a feel of how to best support you through your studies.\\r\\n\\r\\nPlease could you provide me with the following details:\\r\\n\\uf076\\tYour experience \\/ background so far in the child care and\\/or education sector\\r\\n\\uf076\\tWhere or if you are gaining any practical experience during the time on your course\\r\\n\\uf076\\tIf you are gaining any practical experience during the time on your course, the details of the hours \\/sessions that you either work or volunteer for your practical experience, and what type of child care that involves, ie child minding, cr\\u00e8che, play group, day care, schools etc.\\r\\n\\uf076\\tAlso, please also let me know what Unit you are wishing to start with\\r\\nI look forward to hearing from you soon, and starting the process of supporting you through your studies.\\r\\nRegards\\r\\nLinda Broome-Smith\\r\\nNCC \\u2013 Support Tutor \\/ Assessor\\r\\n\\r\\nRegards\\r\\nLinda Broome-Smith\\r\\nNCC \\u2013 Support Tutor\\r\\n\"}', 1517571803, 1, 0, 0),
