(290, 189, 28, '{\"Message\":\"<p>Hi Linda,<\\/p><p>If I am using the information from the underpinning knowledge guide I was given at the same time as my assessment do I still need to write it down on my bibliography? I have used a quote from the internet in some of my answers as well, I haven\'t written the site or the person who has quoted it in the box with the rest of the information but I am going to write it on my bibliography with which box I wrote it in with the quote next to it. Is this okay?<\\/p><p>Kind regards,<\\/p><p>Abbie <br><\\/p>\"}', 1517868253, 1, 0, 0),
(291, 140, 28, '{\"Message\":\"<p>Hi Linda,<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>I have re submitted the assignment with the additional work at the bottom. <\\/p><p>I have copied and pasted the original question and added to the answer. <\\/p><p>I hope that this is correct. <\\/p><p>Thank you <\\/p><p>Lizzie<br><\\/p>\"}', 1517921590, 1, 0, 0),
(292, 129, 28, '{\"Message\":\"<p><span style=\'display: inline !important; float: none; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \\\"Proxima Nova\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-shadow: none; text-transform: none; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;\'>Hi Linda, to answer your question I have no experience with child care and at this present time I don\'t think I will be doing any training whist doing this course. I have started reading through the first module and I have also started doing the assignment. I was wondering if I could send you the beginning bit of the assignment I have done and if you don\'t mind reading through it to see if I\'m on the right track and for your opinion for me to complete the assignment correctly. Thank you, Rhiannon<\\/span><b><\\/b><i><\\/i><u><\\/u><sub><\\/sub><sup><\\/sup><strike><\\/strike><br><\\/p>\"}', 1517927600, 1, 0, 0),
(293, 28, 189, '{\"Message\":\"<p>Hello Abbie<\\/p><p>The internet address should be in your bibliography and in your work.&nbsp; So what you are saying to do makes perfect sense.&nbsp; That will be fine<\\/p><p>Not sure what you mean about what you mean \\\"writing in the boxes\\\"?<\\/p><p>Please do not be constricted in any way, writing your answers into the answer boxes.&nbsp; If you find they wont extend when you are typing or especially if you are completing this by hand....please feel free to just use paper \\/ word etc....as long as you have put the questions criteria number and the whole wording of the question as your headings that will be fine<\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size: 1rem;\\\">Regards<\\/span><br><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size: 1rem;\\\">Linda&nbsp;<\\/span><br><\\/p>\"}', 1517931933, 1, 0, 0),
(294, 28, 140, '{\"Message\":\"<p><span style=\\\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\\\">Hello Elizabeth<\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\\\"><o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\\\">Don\'t worry, I agree this is a tricky one, so here is some\\r\\nadvice for Assignment 1- Question 1.2.3.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\\\">In order to\\r\\nanswer this question, you will need to show your knowledge of child\\r\\ndevelopmental theorists.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\\\">You will need\\r\\nto show that you can identify the theorist and what their theory is and how it\\r\\nis implemented in a school environment.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\\\">The best way\\r\\nto do this is to;<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\\\">1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\\r\\nName the theorist<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\\\">2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\\r\\nName the actual theory and \'BRIEFLY\'&nbsp;explain the bare bones of what\\r\\nthe&nbsp;theory is<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\\\">3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\\r\\nThen explain how it is used in a working environment<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\\\">Please - do\\r\\nnot -&nbsp;re-write the whole text book theory.&nbsp; It&nbsp;is much more\\r\\nimportant that you explain these three points in your own words.&nbsp;<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\\\">This\\r\\nwill&nbsp;prove that you do indeed&nbsp;understand the fundamentals of the\\r\\ntheory and how they can be positively used in a classroom environment.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\\\">For example:<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\\\">You may\\r\\nchoose to talk about Albert Bandura\\u2019s Social Learning Theory, which looks at\\r\\nhow children can learn third party, how to behave&nbsp; by observing the actions and interactions of\\r\\nothers behaviour and their outcomes.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\\\">In your workplace,\\r\\nyou might be able to give an example for instance of a time when you made sure that\\r\\nall positive behaviours were acknowledged, so that others can see and hear the\\r\\npraise.&nbsp; Maybe saying \\u201cThank you Chloe,\\r\\nyou were really good at helping me today.\\u201d and so making it clear that this was\\r\\npositive behaviour and that you were pleased with this.&nbsp; Or maybe by awarding a sticker publically,\\r\\nfor the others to see such as \\u201cLook at Chloe\\u2019s sticker, she was very helpful\\r\\ntoday.&nbsp; Well done\\u201d<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\\\">Another child\\r\\nmay also now wish to help you in order to receive this praise. A child with\\r\\nchallenging behaviour could then be asked if they too would like to help and so\\r\\nreceive the praise and sticker too.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\\\">Also with\\r\\nnegative behaviours a child may be given time out with an explanation of the\\r\\nreasons why.&nbsp; This again may discourage\\r\\nonlookers to also behave in the same way when they see the child having to stop\\r\\nwhat they were enjoying for a while.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\\\">Your example\\r\\nneeds to prove that you do indeed&nbsp;understand the fundamentals of the\\r\\ntheory and how they can be positively used in a classroom environment.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\\\"><o:p>&nbsp;<\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\\\">Also don not\\r\\nforget that there is also a second part to this question.&nbsp; Don\'t forget that the question also wants to\\r\\nknow about how the EYFS is a positive thing and the National Curriculum too<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\\\">&nbsp;Regards\\r\\n- Linda Broome-Smith - tutor<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\\\">&nbsp;<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:9.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\\r\\n&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\\\"><o:p>&nbsp;<\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p>\"}', 1517932116, 1, 0, 0),
