pse: collapse;\\\" border=\\\"1\\\" cellspacing=\\\"0\\\" cellpadding=\\\"0\\\">\\r\\n <tbody><tr style=\\\"mso-yfti-irow:0;mso-yfti-firstrow:yes;mso-yfti-lastrow:yes\\\">\\r\\n  <td width=\\\"616\\\" valign=\\\"top\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0cm 5.4pt; border: 1.33px solid rgb(0, 0, 0); border-image: none; width: 462.1pt; background-color: transparent;\\\">\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 8px 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><b><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>Assessment\\r\\n  Criteria<\\/span><\\/b><b><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Times New Roman\\\",serif; font-size: 12pt;\'> <\\/span><\\/b><b><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>1.<\\/span><\\/b><b style=\\\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>1.1<\\/span><\\/b><\\/p>\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 8px 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>Explain\\r\\n  the sequence and rate of each aspect of development from birth-19 years. <\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n  <\\/td>\\r\\n <\\/tr>\\r\\n<\\/tbody><\\/table>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>In the boxes below, identify the\\r\\nsequence and rate of development for the age of the pupils identified.<span style=\\\"margin: 0px;\\\">&nbsp; <\\/span>You need to remember that all development is\\r\\nholistic and that all children are unique and will develop at their own\\r\\npace.<span style=\\\"margin: 0px;\\\">&nbsp; <\\/span>Your responses below should be\\r\\nfocusing on the developmental norms.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p align=\\\"center\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px 0px 8px 94.53px; text-align: center; line-height: normal; text-indent: -70.9pt;\\\"><b><span style=\'margin: 0px; color: rgb(192, 0, 0); font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 16pt;\'>Birth to 1 Year<\\/span><\\/b><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<table style=\\\"margin: 0px; border: medium; border-image: none; border-collapse: collapse;\\\" border=\\\"1\\\" cellspacing=\\\"0\\\" cellpadding=\\\"0\\\">\\r\\n <tbody><tr style=\\\"mso-yfti-irow:0;mso-yfti-firstrow:yes;height:99.25pt;mso-height-rule:&#10;  exactly\\\">\\r\\n  <td width=\\\"136\\\" valign=\\\"top\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0cm 5.4pt; border: 1.33px solid rgb(0, 0, 0); border-image: none; width: 102.15pt; height: 99.25pt; background-color: transparent;\\\">\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><b style=\\\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>Physical<\\/span><\\/b><\\/p>\\r\\n  <\\/td>\\r\\n  <td width=\\\"480\\\" valign=\\\"top\\\" style=\\\"border-width: 1.33px 1.33px 1.33px 0px; border-style: solid solid solid none; border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 0px; padding: 0cm 5.4pt; border-image: none; width: 359.95pt; height: 99.25pt; background-color: transparent;\\\">\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif;\'>Babies go through incredible physical changes in a short time.\\r\\n  At birth the new-born baby relies on the parent\\/carer as they have minimal\\r\\n  control over there body. However, when they reach their first birthday most\\r\\n  infants have learnt to move their limbs and can roll over to crawl and can\\r\\n  pull themselves up. Some infants have learnt to walk at this age, if they\\r\\n  haven\\u2019t then they will within the next couple of months as each child\\r\\n  develops at there own pace.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n  <\\/td>\\r\\n <\\/tr>\\r\\n <tr style=\\\"mso-yfti-irow:1;height:99.25pt;mso-height-rule:exactly\\\">\\r\\n  <td width=\\\"136\\\" valign=\\\"top\\\" style=\\\"border-width: 0px 1.33px 1.33px; border-style: none solid solid; border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 0px; padding: 0cm 5.4pt; border-image: none; width: 102.15pt; height: 99.25pt; background-color: transparent;\\\">\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><b style=\\\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>Intellectual\\/<\\/span><\\/b><\\/p>\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><b style=\\\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>cognitive<\\/span><\\/b><\\/p>\\r\\n  <\\/td>\\r\\n  <td width=\\\"480\\\" valign=\\\"top\\\" style=\\\"border-width: 0px 1.33px 1.33px 0px; border-style: none solid solid none; border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 0px; padding: 0cm 5.4pt; width: 359.95pt; height: 99.25pt; background-color: transparent;\\\">\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif;\'>In their first month infants begin\\r\\n  to interact with their environment and the people in it. They learn about the\\r\\n  world mainly though their senses of sight and touch. The can recognises\\r\\n  familiar faces such as their parent or caregiver. They can focus on moving\\r\\n  objects and understand that objects still exist even when they cannot see\\r\\n  them.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif;\'>&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif;\'>&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif;\'>&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n  <\\/td>\\r\\n <\\/tr>\\r\\n <tr style=\\\"mso-yfti-irow:2;height:99.25pt;mso-height-rule:exactly\\\">\\r\\n  <td width=\\\"136\\\" valign=\\\"top\\\" style=\\\"border-width: 0px 1.33px 1.33px; border-style: none solid solid; border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 0px; padding: 0cm 5.4pt; border-image: none; width: 102.15pt; height: 99.25pt; background-color: transparent;\\\">\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><b style=\\\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>Communication<\\/span><\\/b><\\/p>\\r\\n  <\\/td>\\r\\n  <td width=\\\"480\\\" valign=\\\"top\\\" style=\\\"border-width: 0px 1.33px 1.33px 0px; border-style: none solid solid none; border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 0px; padding: 0cm 5.4pt; width: 359.95pt; height: 99.25pt; background-color: transparent;\\\">\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif;\'>Babies communicate though their cries, facial expressions\\r\\n  and body language before they learn to speak. If a baby is happy\\/excited,\\r\\n  they will smile and waves there limbs about. If a baby is unhappy\\/sad the\\r\\n  will cry and look for comfort, they will also communicate by babbling away.\\r\\n  By around 10 months babies start to speak using words such as \\u2018mama and\\r\\n  dada\\u2019, and progress with words there onwards. <\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n  <\\/td>\\r\\n <\\/tr>\\r\\n <tr style=\\\"mso-yfti-irow:3;height:99.25pt;mso-height-rule:exactly\\\">\\r\\n  <td width=\\\"136\\\" valign=\\\"top\\\" style=\\\"border-width: 0px 1.33px 1.33px; border-style: none solid solid; border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 0px; padding: 0cm 5.4pt; border-image: none; width: 102.15pt; height: 99.25pt; background-color: transparent;\\\">\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><b style=\\\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>Social,\\r\\n  behavioural, and moral<\\/span><\\/b><\\/p>\\r\\n  <\\/td>\\r\\n  <td width=\\\"480\\\" valign=\\\"top\\\" style=\\\"border-width: 0px 1.33px 1.33px 0px; border-style: none solid solid none; border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 0px; padding: 0cm 5.4pt; width: 359.95pt; height: 99.25pt; background-color: transparent;\\\">\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif;\'>As the baby grows there becomes an increase in their social\\r\\n  interaction also an increase in attachment to caregivers. Coming to the end\\r\\n  of the infants first year they enhance their ability to discover their world\\r\\n  and how things work. Meeting an infant\\u2019s basic needs though consistent care\\r\\n  and positive social interacting at the same time nurtures their moral\\r\\n  development and trust in their caregivers<\\/span><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\'>. <\\/span><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n  <\\/td>\\r\\n <\\/tr>\\r\\n <tr style=\\\"mso-yfti-irow:4;mso-yfti-lastrow:yes;height:99.25pt;mso-height-rule:&#10;  exactly\\\">\\r\\n  <td width=\\\"136\\\" valign=\\\"top\\\" style=\\\"border-width: 0px 1.33px 1.33px; border-style: none solid solid; border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 0px; padding: 0cm 5.4pt; border-image: none; width: 102.15pt; height: 99.25pt; background-color: transparent;\\\">\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><b style=\\\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>Emotional<\\/span><\\/b><\\/p>\\r\\n  <\\/td>\\r\\n  <td width=\\\"480\\\" valign=\\\"top\\\" style=\\\"border-width: 0px 1.33px 1.33px 0px; border-style: none solid solid none; border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 0px; padding: 0cm 5.4pt; width: 359.95pt; height: 99.25pt; background-color: transparent;\\\">\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>To help a baby understand the\\r\\n  world is a safe and welcoming place you need show\\/give them thoughtful care.\\r\\n  Their first relationship is the most important because it will form a close\\r\\n  emotional bond, they will form an attachment to the one they feel closest to.\\r\\n  They will start to show an increase in restlessness and anxiety when they are\\r\\n  around unfamiliar people. <\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n  <p style=\\\"margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\\\"><span style=\'margin: 0px; font-family: \\\"Arial\\\",sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\'>&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n  <\\/td>\\r\\n <\\/tr>\\r\\n<\\/tbody><\\/table>\\r\\n\\r\\n<br>\"}', 1517990235, 1, 0, 0),
